LYNDON B. JOHNSON

President of the United States of America

IO ALL IO WHOM THESE PRESENTS SHALL COME, GREETING:

KNOW YE That, whereas a convention relating to international exhibitions was signed at Paris on November 22, 1928, and two protocols modifying the convention were signed at Paris on

May 10, 1948 and November 16, 1966, all in the French language;

AND WHEREAS the Government of France, as depositary of the convention and protocols, 'has delivered certified texts of them to the Government of the United States of America;

AND WHEREAS the Senate of the United States of America by its resolution of April 30, 1968, two-thirds of the Senators present concurring therein, did advise and consent to the accession to the aforesaid convention and protocols;
